{{Refimprove|date=February 2007}}
'''Spongin''', a modified type of [[collagen]] [[protein]], forms the fibrous [[skeleton]] of most organisms among the phylum [[Porifera]], the sponges. It is secreted by sponge cells known as spongocytes.<ref>{{cite book|last=Anderson |first=D. |title=Invertebrate Zoology |publisher=Oxford University Press |year=2001}}</ref>

Spongin gives a sponge its flexibility. True spongin is found only in members of the class [[Demospongiae]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Brusca |first1=R. |last2=Brusca |first2=G. |title=Invertebrate Zoology |publisher=Sinauer Associates |year=2003 |page=191}}</ref>

